5 Subject: Motor vehicles; operation of vehicles; equipment; inspection
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to limit the
7 instances in which a noncommercial motor vehicle would fail an annual safety
8 inspection and to require inspection station to notify owners of vehicle
9 conditions that may affect safety.
10 An act relating to motor vehicle inspections
11 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
12 Sec. 1. 23 V.S.A. § 1222 is amended to read:
13 § 1222. INSPECTION OF REGISTERED VEHICLES
14 * * *
15 (b)(1)(A) The inspections shall be made at garages or qualified service
16 stations, designated by the Commissioner as inspection stations, for the
17 purpose of determining whether those motor vehicles are properly equipped
18 and maintained in good mechanical condition; provided, however, the.
19 (B)(i) The scope of the safety inspection of a motor vehicle other
20 than a school bus or a commercial motor vehicle shall be limited to parts or
