1 systems that are relevant to the vehicle’s safe operation, and such vehicles shall
2 not fail the safety portion of the inspection unless the condition of the part or
3 system poses or may pose a an imminent danger to the operator or to other
4 highway users.
5 (ii) If a part or system is not in good mechanical condition but
6 does not pose an imminent danger to the operator or other highway users, the
7 inspection station shall provide the owner or operator of the vehicle with
8 written documentation of the condition of the part or system and recommended
9 actions that may be taken to restore the part or system to good mechanical
10 condition. The written documentation shall be signed by the vehicle operator
11 or owner and a copy shall be kept in the motor vehicle.
12 * * *
13 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
14 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
